01:39.641 --> 01:43.395
Yeah, Dad. There's always

01:39.641 --> 01:43.395
a spider on Bacon Day.

01:43.437 --> 01:45.188
You know, I'm not

01:43.437 --> 01:45.188
feeling that good.

01:45.230 --> 01:47.024
I could give Dad

01:45.230 --> 01:47.024
some of mine,

01:47.066 --> 01:49.401
but that's not really

01:47.066 --> 01:49.401
in the true spirit of Bacon Day.

01:49.443 --> 01:50.569
Mom, my stomach hurts.

01:50.611 --> 01:51.820
So does mine.

01:51.862 --> 01:54.322
I'm not kidding,

01:51.862 --> 01:54.322
it's really sore.

01:54.364 --> 01:55.783
Ow! It hurts!

01:55.824 --> 01:56.617
Shut up, Reese.

01:56.658 --> 01:58.159
Mom...

01:56.658 --> 01:58.159
I see spots!

01:58.201 --> 01:59.828
Mommy!

01:59.870 --> 02:01.162
All right, that's enough.

02:01.204 --> 02:02.957
I don't care what test

02:01.204 --> 02:02.957
you didn't study for

02:02.998 --> 02:04.416
or what assignment

02:02.998 --> 02:04.416
you didn't do,

02:04.458 --> 02:05.751
you're going to school.

02:05.793 --> 02:06.877
You know, now that

02:05.793 --> 02:06.877
you mention it...

02:06.919 --> 02:08.378
Everybody's  going.

02:10.213 --> 02:12.173
Sir, what are you doing?

02:12.215 --> 02:13.842
Why are you taking

02:12.215 --> 02:13.842
away our TV?

02:13.884 --> 02:15.844
It's for your

02:13.884 --> 02:15.844
own good, cadet.

02:15.886 --> 02:18.179
But that is the only thing

02:15.886 --> 02:18.179
that makes this place bearable.

02:18.221 --> 02:21.182
Television rots

02:18.221 --> 02:21.182
the mind, cadet.

02:21.224 --> 02:23.018
How can you focus

02:21.224 --> 02:23.018
on your studies

02:23.060 --> 02:24.686
and improve

02:23.060 --> 02:24.686
your character

02:24.728 --> 02:28.607
if your brain is full of

02:24.728 --> 02:28.607
your Morks and your Mindys?

02:28.649 --> 02:31.192
Now you'll have time for

02:28.649 --> 02:31.192
more worthwhile endeavors.

02:31.234 --> 02:33.194
Write a letter. I'm sure

02:31.234 --> 02:33.194
your parole officers

02:33.236 --> 02:35.864
will appreciate

02:33.236 --> 02:35.864
the personal touch.

02:35.906 --> 02:38.700
Okay, that is ridiculous.

02:38.742 --> 02:39.827
I mean, we should do something.

02:39.868 --> 02:41.244
He's right.

02:41.286 --> 02:43.122
Spangler doesn't get

02:41.286 --> 02:43.122
to make arbitrary decisions

02:43.163 --> 02:44.623
about our lives.

02:44.665 --> 02:47.417
He can't tell us

02:44.665 --> 02:47.417
where to go and what to do.

02:47.459 --> 02:49.461
Oh, wait... he can.

02:49.503 --> 02:51.005
Face it, Francis,

02:51.046 --> 02:52.798
we're like prisoners

02:51.046 --> 02:52.798
but without the rights.

02:52.840 --> 02:54.215
Okay, so we're helpless.

02:54.257 --> 02:57.469
But even helpless people

02:54.257 --> 02:57.469
have options.

02:57.511 --> 03:00.055
History is full of supposedly

02:57.511 --> 03:00.055
powerless people

03:00.097 --> 03:03.058
who found a way to stand up

03:00.097 --> 03:03.058
to their oppressors.

03:03.100 --> 03:04.225
What are you talking about?

03:04.267 --> 03:05.894
Civil disobedience.

03:05.936 --> 03:07.646
You know, like a hunger strike.

03:07.688 --> 03:09.272
We could do that.

03:09.314 --> 03:12.233
I mean, he doesn't want a bunch

03:09.314 --> 03:12.233
of starving kids on his hands.

03:12.275 --> 03:13.234
That would totally work.

03:13.276 --> 03:14.235
I don't know.

03:14.277 --> 03:15.320
Isn't that

03:14.277 --> 03:15.320
a bit drastic?

03:15.362 --> 03:16.738
Can't we wait till

03:15.362 --> 03:16.738
after lunch?

03:16.780 --> 03:18.281
What are we having?

03:16.780 --> 03:18.281
Shepherd's pie.

03:18.323 --> 03:20.325
The strike starts now!

03:20.367 --> 03:21.743
(cheering)

03:22.870 --> 03:24.705
Malcolm, why are you

03:22.870 --> 03:24.705
walking like that?

03:24.746 --> 03:26.414
My side still hurts.

03:26.456 --> 03:27.958
But it's the weekend.

03:32.963 --> 03:34.715
Okay, everybody get in the car.

03:34.756 --> 03:36.717
We're going to the hospital.

03:39.511 --> 03:42.263
Mom, why does that man

03:39.511 --> 03:42.263
have a lightbulb stuck...

03:42.305 --> 03:45.100
Dewey, get away from there.

03:45.809 --> 03:47.102
Dad, you okay?

03:47.144 --> 03:48.145
I'm fine, son.

03:48.187 --> 03:50.147
Just not a big fan

03:48.187 --> 03:50.147
of hospitals.

03:50.189 --> 03:52.315
Oh, they can dress it up

03:50.189 --> 03:52.315
with plants and pictures,

03:52.357 --> 03:55.276
but let's face it, this

03:52.357 --> 03:55.276
place is a slaughterhouse.

03:55.318 --> 03:56.361
Hal...

03:57.487 --> 03:58.572
Okay, we've run some tests.

03:58.613 --> 04:00.281
His white count is 12.2,

04:00.323 --> 04:01.992
and with these acute

04:00.323 --> 04:01.992
abdominal pains,

04:02.034 --> 04:04.369
I'm pretty sure we're

04:02.034 --> 04:04.369
looking at appendicitis.

04:04.411 --> 04:05.453
We'll hold him

04:05.495 --> 04:06.997
for observation tonight,

04:07.039 --> 04:09.166
and then tomorrow

04:07.039 --> 04:09.166
he'll probably need surgery.

04:09.208 --> 04:10.375
I'm having surgery?

04:10.417 --> 04:12.293
There's nothing

04:10.417 --> 04:12.293
to worry about, son.

04:12.335 --> 04:14.295
You'll barely even have

04:12.335 --> 04:14.295
a scar.

04:14.337 --> 04:16.297
If you can just sign

04:14.337 --> 04:16.297
these release forms,

04:16.339 --> 04:18.133
we'll check him in.

04:18.175 --> 04:19.760
They're going

04:18.175 --> 04:19.760
to cut you open?

04:19.801 --> 04:21.220
Like a trout.

04:21.261 --> 04:22.387
Don't worry,

04:21.261 --> 04:22.387
you won't feel a thing;

04:22.429 --> 04:23.471
you'll be unconscious.

04:23.513 --> 04:24.973
Not necessarily.

04:25.015 --> 04:27.142
I saw this thing on TV

04:25.015 --> 04:27.142
where this guy woke up

04:27.184 --> 04:28.393
in the middle

04:27.184 --> 04:28.393
of his operation

04:28.435 --> 04:30.395
and could feel everything

04:28.435 --> 04:30.395
they were doing,

04:30.437 --> 04:34.315
but he was paralyzed

04:30.437 --> 04:34.315
and couldn't even scream.

04:34.357 --> 04:36.484
Reese, for the love of God,

04:34.357 --> 04:36.484
stop talking.

04:36.526 --> 04:38.112
Mom...

04:36.526 --> 04:38.112
Honey, don't worry about it.

04:38.153 --> 04:39.529
You're going to have

04:38.153 --> 04:39.529
your own TV,

04:39.571 --> 04:40.948
you're going to have

04:39.571 --> 04:40.948
people to wait on you;

04:40.989 --> 04:42.241
it's going to be

04:40.989 --> 04:42.241
a lot better

04:42.282 --> 04:43.366
than being at home.

04:46.078 --> 04:48.205
Why do I have to stay

04:46.078 --> 04:48.205
in the kids' ward?

04:48.247 --> 04:49.957
I'm sorry, honey,

04:48.247 --> 04:49.957
but you're six months too young

04:49.998 --> 04:50.999
to have an adult room.

04:51.041 --> 04:52.333
I hear if you're

04:51.041 --> 04:52.333
really good,

04:52.375 --> 04:55.045
they'll put apple juice

04:52.375 --> 04:55.045
in your sippy cup.

04:55.087 --> 04:56.337
(Hal whimpering)

04:56.379 --> 04:58.339
Dad, do you want to

04:56.379 --> 04:58.339
wait out in the car?

04:58.381 --> 04:59.800
(inhales deeply)

04:59.841 --> 05:01.384
No. I'm okay.

05:01.426 --> 05:03.220
I'm fine.

05:03.262 --> 05:04.972
I'm on a beach.

05:05.013 --> 05:07.348
There's the surf,

05:05.013 --> 05:07.348
there's sand,

05:07.390 --> 05:09.350
there's... needles.

05:09.392 --> 05:13.396
There's the horrible choking

05:09.392 --> 05:13.396
stench of hospital antiseptic.

05:13.438 --> 05:14.439
Hal!

05:14.481 --> 05:15.774
Coming.

05:15.816 --> 05:17.358
I think I better take

05:15.816 --> 05:17.358
your father home.

05:17.400 --> 05:18.819
You'll be okay.

05:22.405 --> 05:24.449
Hey, feel better, sport.

05:25.700 --> 05:26.994
Reese, give

05:25.700 --> 05:26.994
your brother a hug.

05:27.035 --> 05:28.036
Aw, Mom.

05:28.078 --> 05:29.704
Do it!

05:31.498 --> 05:33.000
If you tell anyone

05:31.498 --> 05:33.000
I hugged you,

05:33.041 --> 05:34.459
I'll put you

05:33.041 --> 05:34.459
right back in here.

05:35.502 --> 05:37.296
Bye.

05:38.421 --> 05:40.882
Why did she make him hug me?

05:42.467 --> 05:45.637
Wait.

05:42.467 --> 05:45.637
Why  did  she make him hug me?

05:46.888 --> 05:49.390
Wow, it's sure quiet

05:46.888 --> 05:49.390
without Malcolm here.

05:49.432 --> 05:50.684
Poor little guy.

05:50.725 --> 05:52.393
There's an extra pork chop.

05:50.725 --> 05:52.393
Mine!

05:54.896 --> 05:56.273
Go ahead. I'm stuffed.

05:56.315 --> 05:57.107
Me, too.

05:57.149 --> 05:58.483
So am I.

05:58.525 --> 06:00.694
I was just hoping someone

05:58.525 --> 06:00.694
